<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,917,1120]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName authority="Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier &amp; Mokhtari &amp; Rakhshani &amp; Gilasian, 2017" authorityName="Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier &amp; Mokhtari &amp; Rakhshani &amp; Gilasian" authorityYear="2017" box="[189,467,917,943]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Dasydorylas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derafshani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,467,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Dasydorylas derafshani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[473,561,918,944]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Becker, 1908)" baseAuthorityName="Becker" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[792,1090,917,943]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Dasydorylas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[792,910,918,943]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">D. setosus</emphasis>
(Becker, 1908)
</taxonomicName>
, redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kehlmaier C." pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="45 - 353" refId="ref6914" refString="Kehlmaier C. 2005 a. Taxonomic revision of European Eudorylini (Insecta, Diptera, Pipunculidae). Verhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg (Neue Folge) 41: 45 - 353." type="journal article" year="2005">Kehlmaier (2005a)</bibRefCitation>
and known from the Canary Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[733,839,953,979]" name="Morocco" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Morocco</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[899,969,952,978]" name="Spain" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Spain</collectingCountry>
, and to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kehlmaier, 2005" authorityName="Kehlmaier" authorityYear="2005" box="[1066,1394,952,979]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Dasydorylas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gradus">
<emphasis box="[1066,1184,952,978]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">D. gradus</emphasis>
Kehlmaier, 2005
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[380,445,987,1013]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Israel</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kehlmaier C." box="[496,728,987,1014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref6949" refString="Kehlmaier C. 2005 b. Taxonomic studies on Palaearctic and Oriental Eudorylini (Diptera: Pipunculidae), with the description of three new species. Zootaxa 1030: 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1030.1.1" type="journal article" year="2005">Kehlmaier (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
. The males of all three species have long spines at the apex of the phallic guide that differ in number and direction between species, with 
<taxonomicName authority="Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier &amp; Mokhtari &amp; Rakhshani &amp; Gilasian, 2017" authorityName="Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier &amp; Mokhtari &amp; Rakhshani &amp; Gilasian" authorityYear="2017" box="[1192,1355,1023,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Dasydorylas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derafshani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1192,1355,1023,1049]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">D. derafshani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
having eight downward directed spines on either side. Additional diagnostic characters are the differently shaped surstyli and, compared to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Becker" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[707,827,1094,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Pipunculidae" genus="Dasydorylas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[707,827,1094,1119]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">D. setosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the shorter and more pilose scutellar hair fringe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,324,1159,1185]" box="[189,324,1159,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1159,1185]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1159,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1205,1267]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
This species is named in honour of Hossein Ali Derafshan, who collected the 
<typeStatus box="[1109,1160,1206,1232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">type</typeStatus>
series material. The surname is to be used as a noun in genitive case.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
