<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,334,1694,1720]" box="[189,334,1694,1720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1694,1720]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1694,1720]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,760,1741,1803]" box="[234,298,1741,1767]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1741,1767]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,760,1741,1803]" box="[189,760,1776,1803]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,498,1776,1803]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.7 mm</quantity>
(excluding antennae).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1398,1841,2009]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
HEAD. Face dark, silver-gray pollinose. Scape dark, pedicel brown with a pair of short upper bristles and one short lower bristle; flagellum yellow, short tapering and gray pollinose (LF:WF=2–2.2); arista dark, flattened, with thickened base. Eyes converging but not meeting and separated by less than diameter of frontal facets (
<figureCitation box="[358,450,1947,1973]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1940,1966]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,1449,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,1449,1898]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype. A. Lateral view. B. Dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836550" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836550/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Frons dark, silver-gray pollinose; vertex dark, lacking pollinosity; occiput dark, gray pollinose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,267,435]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
THORAX. Pleura, prescutum, scutum and scutellum dark but prescutum light yellow at lateral margin. Pleura gray pollinose. Postpronotal lobe pale, gray pollinose and with 3–5 postpronotal setae along upper margin. Prescutum and scutum gray pollinose, with two uniseriate dorsocentral rows of conspicuous setae and supra-alar setae. Scutellum gray pollinose, with an apical fringe of up to ten pale setae (up to 
<quantity box="[189,284,408,435]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
). Subscutellum gray pollinose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,473,576]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
WING. Length: 
<quantity box="[368,514,473,500]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="3.4" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.5 mm</quantity>
. LW:MWW=3–3.2. Wing almost entirely covered with microtrichia. Only small basal cells of wings, e.g., bc, basal of cell c, br, cell bm, basal of cup with somewhat reduced microtrichia. Pterostigma brown and complete (LS:LTC =1.0, LTC:LFC =1.1). M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1147,1156,562,576]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">1</subScript>
gently undulating.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1398,609,671]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
HALTER. Length: 
<quantity box="[393,489,610,636]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
. Base dark, stem narrowly white and knob paler than base, somewhat gray pollinose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,710,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">LEGS. Coxae dark but yellow on apical margin, gray pollinose. Mid coxa with three brown anterior bristles. Trochanters light brown, partly gray pollinose. Femora dark, distinctly light brown at apex, gray pollinose. All femora bearing two rows of dark, smaller, peg-like anteroventral spines on apical one third. Tibiae light brown, distinctly dark on apical half, gray pollinose with three rows of brown setae on anterior and posterior sides, without apical spines. Hind tibia with a wrinkled indentation midanteriorly. Tarsi light brown and paler than apical half of tibiae, brown pollinose, with some black setae dorsally. Distitarsi brown. Pulvilli shorter than distitarsi.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1399,986,1224]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">ABDOMEN. Ground colour dark. Tergite 1 with four to five brown lateral bristles. Tergites 1–5 with brown setae. Tergites 1–2 gray pollinose laterally and dorsally, and tergites 3–5 gray pollinose laterally extending onto dorsal surface along posterior margin. Tergite 5 asymmetrical. LT35:WT5= 1.4, WT5:LT5 =2.1 and T5R:T5L=1.1. Syntergosternite 8 dark, gray pollinose, without dorsal depression on side of left surstylus. LT35:WS8 =2.2. Viewed laterally, syntergosternite 8 higher than long (LS8:HS8= 0.6). Viewed caudally, membranous area about one third of the width of syntergosternite 8, vertically directed, broader in upper half.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1398,1263,1396]" lastBlockId="5.[189,1399,267,469]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
GENITALIA. Genital capsule in dorsal view: epandrium dark but brownish near surstyli and tergite 5, gray pollinose and longer than wide (MLE:MWE= 1.5). Surstyli paler than epandrium, gray pollinose and symmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[352,445,1334,1360]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,747,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,741,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Terminalia of Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype.A. Phallic guide, gonopods and hypandrium in ventral view. B. Phallus and membranous sheet in lateral view. C. Phallic guide in lateral view. D. Ejaculatory apodeme. E. Surstyli in dorsal view. F. Left surstylus in lateral view. G. Right surstylus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836552/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Both with a broad and rectangular base and a pair of finger-like projections at apices which are bent towards each other by 45° (
<figureCitation box="[783,876,1369,1395]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,747,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,741,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Terminalia of Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype.A. Phallic guide, gonopods and hypandrium in ventral view. B. Phallus and membranous sheet in lateral view. C. Phallic guide in lateral view. D. Ejaculatory apodeme. E. Surstyli in dorsal view. F. Left surstylus in lateral view. G. Right surstylus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836552/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). Genital capsule in ventral view: gonopods rather large and almost symmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[627,721,267,293]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,747,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,741,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Terminalia of Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype.A. Phallic guide, gonopods and hypandrium in ventral view. B. Phallus and membranous sheet in lateral view. C. Phallic guide in lateral view. D. Ejaculatory apodeme. E. Surstyli in dorsal view. F. Left surstylus in lateral view. G. Right surstylus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); phallus trifid, narrow, with long and straight ejaculatory ducts (
<figureCitation box="[270,366,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,747,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,741,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Terminalia of Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype.A. Phallic guide, gonopods and hypandrium in ventral view. B. Phallus and membranous sheet in lateral view. C. Phallic guide in lateral view. D. Ejaculatory apodeme. E. Surstyli in dorsal view. F. Left surstylus in lateral view. G. Right surstylus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); phallic guide of medium length, rather broad, on either side with eight downwards directed long spines at its apex (
<figureCitation box="[565,658,338,364]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,747,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,741,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Terminalia of Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype.A. Phallic guide, gonopods and hypandrium in ventral view. B. Phallus and membranous sheet in lateral view. C. Phallic guide in lateral view. D. Ejaculatory apodeme. E. Surstyli in dorsal view. F. Left surstylus in lateral view. G. Right surstylus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Genital capsule in lateral view: epandrium without projecting lobe on either side. Both surstyli distinctly convex and broad in basal two thirds, distally narrowed to form a pair of finger-like processes which are bent towards each other (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1086,408,434]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,747,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,741,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Terminalia of Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype.A. Phallic guide, gonopods and hypandrium in ventral view. B. Phallus and membranous sheet in lateral view. C. Phallic guide in lateral view. D. Ejaculatory apodeme. E. Surstyli in dorsal view. F. Left surstylus in lateral view. G. Right surstylus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
F–G). Phallic guide broad, gently bent towards surstyli (
<figureCitation box="[530,623,443,469]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,747,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,741,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Terminalia of Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype.A. Phallic guide, gonopods and hypandrium in ventral view. B. Phallus and membranous sheet in lateral view. C. Phallic guide in lateral view. D. Ejaculatory apodeme. E. Surstyli in dorsal view. F. Left surstylus in lateral view. G. Right surstylus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme funnel-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1082,1176,443,469]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,747,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,741,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Terminalia of Dasydorylas derafshani Motamedinia &amp; Kehlmaier sp. nov., ♂, paratype.A. Phallic guide, gonopods and hypandrium in ventral view. B. Phallus and membranous sheet in lateral view. C. Phallic guide in lateral view. D. Ejaculatory apodeme. E. Surstyli in dorsal view. F. Left surstylus in lateral view. G. Right surstylus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
